## Refactor proposal for `src/Card.tsx`

Below is one consolidated rewrite, then a finding-by-finding rationale so each change is traceable.

```tsx
import styles from "./Card.module.css";

type CardProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  onActivate?: () => void;
};

export function Card({ children, onActivate }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <button type="button" className={styles.card} onClick={onActivate}>
      <div className={styles.body}>{children}</div>
      <aside className={styles.sidebar}>sidebar</aside>
    </button>
  );
}
```

```css
/* Card.module.css */
.card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) clamp(180px, 25%, 240px);
  gap: var(--space-4);
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--size-card-max, 64rem);
  padding: var(--space-6);
  background: var(--color-surface-accent);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  text-align: left;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.card:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--color-focus); outline-offset: 2px; }

.body    { font-size: var(--text-md); }
.sidebar { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); }

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```

### Tied to each finding

- **`accessible_interaction_risk` (crime_00001)** — line 10's `<div onClick>` becomes a real `<button type="button">`. That gets keyboard focus, Enter/Space activation, and an implicit `role="button"` for free. `:focus-visible` provides a visible focus ring. If the surrounding semantics actually call for a link, swap to `<a href>`; only fall back to `role="button" tabIndex={0}` plus a keydown handler if neither element fits.

- **`design_token_escape` (crime_00002)** — the nine inline hex/rgb/px literals (`#ff00aa`, `#0a0a0a`, `#cccccc`, `#1a73e8`, `rgb(0,0,0)`, `24`, etc.) move out of the JSX `style` prop and into CSS custom properties (`--color-*`, `--space-*`, `--radius-*`, `--shadow-*`). Future edits — human or agent — read from the design system instead of forking new literals. If tokens don't exist yet, add them to the theme module rather than reintroducing raw values.

- **`responsive_fragility` (crime_00003)** — the three fixed widths (`800px`, `720px`, `240px`) and the hard-coded `18px` font are replaced with `width: 100%`, `max-width` against a token, a fluid `grid-template-columns` using `minmax` + `clamp`, and a `@media (max-width: 640px)` rule that collapses the sidebar under the body. Typography uses token-driven `rem` sizes so it scales with user settings.

### Notes on scope

- The fixture file has no `Card.module.css` today — creating it is part of the refactor. If the project standard is Tailwind or `styled-components`, the same mapping applies (token classes / theme references replacing literals).
- I haven't touched the file yet — flag if you'd like me to apply the edits to the fixture, or keep this as a written proposal for the eval.
